data.description: Close your eyes and imagine, stepping into this 3-bedroom, 2-bath home in Port Tampa's peaceful neighborhood. As you approach, you're greeted by the warm, inviting facade of the house, a promise of comfort and serenity.Upon entering, the spacious layout unfolds before you. Picture the large bonus room, where the possibilities are endless - perhaps it's your home office, a cozy den, or even a playroom for the kids. Natural light filters through the windows, casting a soft, welcoming glow.Now, you wander into the backyard. The door opens to reveal a vast, fenced oasis. Tall, majestic trees provide shade and tranquility, making it the perfect spot for a leisurely afternoon barbecue, a game of catch, or simply lounging with a good book.As you stand there, you can't help but appreciate the convenience of being near MacDill Air Force Base, Picnic Island Beach, along with the stadiums of the Tampa Bay Buccaneers, Lightning, and Rays, (the list goes on) adds to the appeal of this location.This home isn't just a property; it's a canvas for you to paint the picture of a comfortable, vibrant life in the heart of South Tampa. Envision your life here, the potential is boundless.  (THE OFFICE ADDS AN EXTRA 220 SQUARE FEET OF LIVING SPACE)
